The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Sachin needs 3-4 weeks to recover
                                                                                                                                                                                                       Sachin needs 3-4 weeks to recover
            OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT            Sachin Tendulkar                           
	Colombo: Sachin Tendulkar, who landed on his left elbow while attempting a catch in Sri Lankas first innings in the decider, requires three-four weeks to recover from the injury.         
	While he has been replaced (by Subramaniam Badrinath) in the squad for the five ODIs, there could also be a question mark over his participation in next months Champions Trophy in Pakistan.         
	Indias first match, against holders Australia, is in Lahore on September 13.         
	I need three-four weeks to get fit... As you can see, the elbow is swollen... Lets see how things go, Sachin told The Telegraph on Monday evening.         
	Hell be leaving for home on Tuesday.                                                                                                                          
